2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 341
BY REPRESENTATIVE TERRY LANDRY
JUDGES/JUSTICE OF PEACE: Requests the Louisiana State Law Institute to conduct a
study of the handling of eviction proceedings by justice of the peace courts
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To authorize and direct the Louisiana State Law Institute to conduct a study of how justice
3 of the peace courts handle eviction proceedings and how structure of the courts,
4 funding, and procedures impact fairness and outcomes for tenants and landlords.
5 WHEREAS, justice of the peace courts are statutorily authorized by R.S. 13:2586
6 and have concurrent jurisdiction with the district courts in all civil matters; and
7 WHEREAS, there are three-hundred ninety justice of the peace courts in this state;
8 and
9 WHEREAS, justice of the peace courts operate under different and more limited
10 procedural protections for litigants than the district courts; and
11 WHEREAS, legal training of individuals holding judgeships, including ethics,
12 conflicts of interest, and continuing education, should be required to ensure qualification for
13 the duties they perform; and
14 WHEREAS, evictions carry significant social and economic consequences; and
15 WHEREAS, financial incentives, including the filing fees received and retained by
16 the justice of the peace courts from eviction proceedings, could lead to higher evictions and
17 a bias for landlords; and
18 WHEREAS, a discussion regarding the operations of these courts, the training
19 provided, the audit of operations, the method of funding, and related expenditures is
20 necessary; and
