1 WHEREAS, a study by the Louisiana State Law Institute is necessary to provide data
2 and recommendations to the legislature to develop potential reforms that improve fairness,
3 transparency, and consistency in eviction proceedings.
4 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
5 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby authorize and direct the Louisiana State Law Institute
6 to conduct a study of how justice of the peace courts handle eviction proceedings and how
7 structure of the courts, funding, and procedures impact fairness and outcomes for tenants and
8 landlords, and to provide a report to the legislature no later than February 1, 2027.
9 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Louisiana State Law Institute shall submit
10 one print copy and one electronic copy of any report produced pursuant to the Resolution
11 to the David R. Poynter Legislative Research Library as required by R.S. 24:772.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
13 director of the Louisiana State Law Institute.
